**Configuration Pattern:**

```typescript
// open-ai.service.ts - Lines 1-23
import { Injectable, Logger } from '@nestjs/common';
import { OpenAI } from 'openai';
import { getEnv } from '@utils/get-env-variable.util';
import { OPENAI_API_KEY } from '@constants/env-variables.constant';

export interface ProductFeatureResponse {
    description?: string[];
    error?: string;
}

@Injectable()
export class OpenAIService {
    private readonly logger = new Logger(OpenAIService.name);
    private readonly openai: OpenAI;

    constructor() {
        const apiKey = getEnv<string>({ key: OPENAI_API_KEY });
        this.openai = new OpenAI({ apiKey, baseURL: 'https://api.openai.com/v1' });
    }
}
```

**Key Patterns:**
- Uses the official `openai` npm package
- Stores OpenAI client as private instance variable
- Gets API key via `getEnv()` utility (never accesses `process.env` directly)
- Imports API key constant from `@constants/env-variables.constant`

**Module Structure:**

```typescript
// open-ai.module.ts
@Module({
    providers: [OpenAIService],
    exports: [OpenAIService],
})
export class OpenAIModule {}
```

**API Call Pattern:**

```typescript
// open-ai.service.ts - Lines 57-71
private async getOpenAIResponse(prompt: string): Promise<ProductFeatureResponse> {
    const completion = await this.openai.chat.completions.create({
        messages: [
            {
                role: 'system',
                content: `You are an expert in data preprocessing and feature engineering...`,
            },
            { role: 'user', content: [{ type: 'text', text: prompt }] },
        ],
        model: 'gpt-4o',
        response_format: { type: 'json_object' },
    });

    if (!completion.choices[0]) {
        return { error: 'No response from OpenAI' };
    }

    const content = completion.choices[0].message.content;
    if (!content) {
        return { error: 'Empty response from OpenAI' };
    }

    try {
        const parsedResponse = JSON.parse(content) as ProductFeatureResponse;
        // ... response handling logic
        return parsedResponse;
    } catch (parseError) {
        this.logger.error('Failed to parse OpenAI response:', parseError);
        return { error: 'Failed to parse OpenAI response' };
    }
}
```

**Error Handling Strategy:**
- Returns error objects instead of throwing (graceful degradation)
- Logs errors using NestJS Logger
- Handles parse errors, empty responses, and API errors

